<subSubSection id="C3536518424FFFAEFF5A360F0773E338" pageId="3" pageNumber="282" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF63693424FFFAEFF5A360F0773E338" blockId="3.[151,1436,152,591]" pageId="3" pageNumber="282">
<emphasis id="B93DEA81424FFFAEFF5A360F0261E04E" bold="true" box="[199,329,360,383]" pageId="3" pageNumber="282">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C494D10424FFFAEFECC36000106E04E" authorityName="♂ Griswold" authorityYear="2018" box="[337,558,359,383]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stenoheriades" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifida">
<emphasis id="B93DEA81424FFFAEFECC36000106E04E" box="[337,558,359,383]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="282">Stenoheriades bifida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not fit in any of the four species groups previously identified by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD84B62424FFFAEFAA5360F03C9E090" author="Griswold" pageId="3" pageNumber="282" refString="Griswold, T. L. (1985) A generic and subgeneric revision of the Heriades genus-group. Doctoral Dissertation. Utah State University, Logan, Utah, xii + 165 pp." type="book" year="1985">Griswold (1985)</bibRefCitation>
. It shares with the 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D10424FFFAEFE3436ED01A1E090" authority="Griswold" authorityName="Griswold" box="[425,649,394,417]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stenoheriades" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prionota">
<emphasis id="B93DEA81424FFFAEFE3436ED0108E090" box="[425,544,394,417]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="282">S. prionota</emphasis>
Griswold
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D10424FFFAEFD2036ED00FDE090" authority="(Cockerell)" authorityName="Cockerell" baseAuthorityName="Cockerell" baseAuthorityYear="1932" box="[701,981,393,417]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stenoheriades" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="livingstonei">
<emphasis id="B93DEA81424FFFAEFD2036ED007CE090" box="[701,852,393,417]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="282">S. livingstonei</emphasis>
(Cockerell)
</taxonomicName>
species groups the absence of preoccipital carinae, absence of juxtantennal carinae, absence of omaular carinae, and the presence of a crenulate carina on T6. It differs from these two species groups in the presence of horizontal grooves dorsally on the metepisternum, the serate hypostomal carina, the bispinose T7, and the polished, concave, and apically projected S2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3536518424FFFAEFF5A357201F3E37E" pageId="3" pageNumber="282" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BF63693424FFFAEFF5A357201F3E37E" blockId="3.[151,1436,152,591]" pageId="3" pageNumber="282">
<emphasis id="B93DEA81424FFFAEFF5A3572026FE31D" bold="true" box="[199,327,533,556]" pageId="3" pageNumber="282">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is taken from the Latin ‘bifida’, a feminine adjective in the nominative singular, in reference to the distinctive elongate twin spines of T7.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
